    "records/notes/initial-brain-dump-e4f2a891.json": {
      "$schema": "https://srs.semanticops.com/schema/2.0/note.json",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-25T00:00:00Z",
      "instanceId": "e4f2a891-3c7d-4b5e-9f12-8a6d0b1c2e3f",
      "sections": [
        {
          "content": "Put art in the back stairwell of the town hall. Immo has work. Sam and Brian can do the mounting. Lets just try it. The space is underused and a bit grim - it could be something. Not a gallery exactly. More like making the building interesting to be in.",
          "name": "the_idea"
        },
        {
          "content": "Immo - has the work and the eye. Would need to be curatorial lead, he should pick what goes up.\nSam - his building, or close to it. Party Utility liaison. Knows what we can and cant fix to walls. Nothing happens without him knowing.\nBrian - practical, knows how to mount things properly.\nPeter - holding the project together, writing things down.",
          "name": "people"
        },
        {
          "content": "Its Limehouse Town Hall. Party Utility runs it. The back stairwell is the obvious place to start - its ours to use and nobody has done anything with it. The main hallway might come later but thats more complicated, more visible, more people have opinions.\nWe cannot leave the walls in a worse state than we found them. That has to be a given. Whatever we put up has to come down cleanly or be finished properly.",
          "name": "building"
        },
        {
          "content": "Not a commercial gallery. Not trying to be one. We dont own the work. We just show it. We dont manage the building - we work inside it.",
          "name": "what_we_are_not"
        },
        {
          "content": "How long do we run this? Is it permanent or are we doing a pilot?\nDo we need formal sign-off from Party Utility or does Sam being involved cover that?\nWhat happens to the work if we stop - whos responsible for getting it back to the artists?\nAre other tenants going to have views about this?\nDo we need to insure the work? Probably not but we should think about it.\nPainting - the walls are not great. Does the work need a clean ground or can we work with what we have?",
          "name": "open_questions"
        },
        {
          "content": "Keep it simple. Start small. Back stairs only. Get one show up and see how it feels. We can always extend. Harder to walk back something that got complicated.",
          "name": "instinct"
        },
        {
          "content": "Walked the space in the meeting. More wall than we thought - the whole run of the stairwell plus the hallway into the back office. Old plaster walls. Not solid. If you keep drilling you crumble them. The back hallway could do with some TLC but thats not a blocker. Lighting is a separate problem - existing fittings are there but not ideal. Summer show might not need it resolved because its a sauna up there anyway and gets natural light most of the day.",
          "name": "space_assessment"
        },
        {
          "content": "Long discussion about how to hang things. Hanging rails came up early - ruled out, looks institutional and inflexible for this space. Command strips - Brian has bad experience taking them down, Sam says they always fail in this building after a week or so. The walls need to be completely grease-free and they are not. Something permanent seems right but we are not sure yet whether that means simple plugs and screws or something more engineered. Brian had ideas about bars, bolts, a sacrificial layer. We did not land anywhere by the end of this phase.",
          "name": "mounting_first_thoughts"
        }
      ],
      "tags": [],
      "title": "Initial brain dump"
    },
    "records/tier-2/article-0482c489.json": {
      "createdAt": "2026-05-31T14:55:35.184158383+00:00",
      "fieldValues": [
        {
          "fieldId": "60be1468-01bc-5d12-9eea-628f02801893",
          "value": "A-004"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "d7e82557-9045-5e92-a494-d99112bbec4a",
          "value": "How we make decisions"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "8aa3eba2-204b-5ebd-ba7a-be0f066027d6",
          "value": "Decisions are made by talk and agreement. We do not vote. Where we cannot agree, the matter stays open or is recorded as an exercise. Once a decision is agreed, it is written down in the decision log and does not change silently — a new decision supersedes an old one by name. These Articles may be amended by unanimous agreement of all current members. The Clerk is responsible for maintaining the coherence of the record."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "3340532b-d845-5e54-92b3-819ed05365c5",
          "value": "Writing things down is the mechanism by which we hold ourselves accountable and remain honest with artists who exhibit with us."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "1f01bc6b-39c8-58d7-b1a3-79142623fece",
          "value": "Unanimous agreement of all current members."
        }
      ],
      "instanceId": "0482c489-37b4-4342-adaa-36e69dc6f780",
      "lifecycleState": "ratified",
      "typeId": "a1142ac3-5385-5c0e-8630-1dd3432cdf7f",
      "typeName": "article",
      "typeNamespace": "governance",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-08T21:05:17.133891065+00:00"
    },
    "records/tier-2/article-31291422.json": {
      "createdAt": "2026-05-31T14:55:35.173940496+00:00",
      "fieldValues": [
        {
          "fieldId": "60be1468-01bc-5d12-9eea-628f02801893",
          "value": "A-002"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "d7e82557-9045-5e92-a494-d99112bbec4a",
          "value": "What we are here to do"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "8aa3eba2-204b-5ebd-ba7a-be0f066027d6",
          "value": "LiMoMa exists to curate, install, and maintain a rotating display of artwork in the back stairwell and landings of the building. We select work, agree on placement, and manage the practical business of mounting and demounting. We are not a commercial gallery: we do not sell work on behalf of artists, take commission, or enter into financial relationships with artists in exchange for showing their work."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "3340532b-d845-5e54-92b3-819ed05365c5",
          "value": "Stating what we are not — a commercial gallery — is as important as stating what we are. This protects artists who exhibit with us and is honest about our amateur, community basis."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "1f01bc6b-39c8-58d7-b1a3-79142623fece",
          "value": "Unanimous agreement of all current members."
        }
      ],
      "instanceId": "31291422-cd8b-4840-b884-d55023d938cb",
      "lifecycleState": "ratified",
      "typeId": "a1142ac3-5385-5c0e-8630-1dd3432cdf7f",
      "typeName": "article",
      "typeNamespace": "governance",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-08T21:05:17.266092197+00:00"
    },
    "records/tier-2/article-7560efe9.json": {
      "createdAt": "2026-05-31T14:55:35.178917705+00:00",
      "fieldValues": [
        {
          "fieldId": "60be1468-01bc-5d12-9eea-628f02801893",
          "value": "A-003"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "d7e82557-9045-5e92-a494-d99112bbec4a",
          "value": "Who we are"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "8aa3eba2-204b-5ebd-ba7a-be0f066027d6",
          "value": "The founding members of LiMoMa are Sam Hayder, Immo Klink, Peter Brownell, and Brian. New members may be admitted by agreement of all current members. Membership carries no financial obligation. Any member may resign at any time without formality. The group has no quorum rules during the pilot phase: decisions require that all members have had a reasonable opportunity to be heard."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "1f01bc6b-39c8-58d7-b1a3-79142623fece",
          "value": "Unanimous agreement of all current members. Admission of a new member requires unanimous agreement."
        }
      ],
      "instanceId": "7560efe9-27e3-4186-8b9d-6ab48283f1df",
      "lifecycleState": "ratified",
      "typeId": "a1142ac3-5385-5c0e-8630-1dd3432cdf7f",
      "typeName": "article",
      "typeNamespace": "governance",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-08T21:05:17.363275919+00:00"
    },
    "records/tier-2/article-ad159754.json": {
      "createdAt": "2026-05-31T14:55:35.167441369+00:00",
      "fieldValues": [
        {
          "fieldId": "60be1468-01bc-5d12-9eea-628f02801893",
          "value": "A-001"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "d7e82557-9045-5e92-a494-d99112bbec4a",
          "value": "What this is"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "8aa3eba2-204b-5ebd-ba7a-be0f066027d6",
          "value": "LiMoMa — the Limehouse Museum of Maybe Art — is a community gallery initiative that uses the back stairs and landings of Limehouse Town Hall as a space for exhibiting artwork. It exists as a voluntary association of members with no formal legal status. The pilot runs for six months from June 2026."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "3340532b-d845-5e54-92b3-819ed05365c5",
          "value": "The name and definition set the frame for all subsequent decisions. 'Maybe Art' signals that the space is exploratory — not a conventional gallery with commercial or institutional expectations."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "1f01bc6b-39c8-58d7-b1a3-79142623fece",
          "value": "Unanimous agreement of all current members."
        }
      ],
      "instanceId": "ad159754-2edd-4bf8-a70f-a29a617e5809",
      "lifecycleState": "ratified",
      "typeId": "a1142ac3-5385-5c0e-8630-1dd3432cdf7f",
      "typeName": "article",
      "typeNamespace": "governance",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-08T21:05:17.461645865+00:00"
    },
    "records/tier-2/article-c503fae5.json": {
      "createdAt": "2026-05-31T14:55:35.188976549+00:00",
      "fieldValues": [
        {
          "fieldId": "60be1468-01bc-5d12-9eea-628f02801893",
          "value": "A-005"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "d7e82557-9045-5e92-a494-d99112bbec4a",
          "value": "Care of the building"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "8aa3eba2-204b-5ebd-ba7a-be0f066027d6",
          "value": "We will leave the building in no worse condition than we found it. Installation work must be carried out carefully: minimum drilled holes, no continuous re-drilling into the same plaster, and all fixings made good when removed. The member with Building Authority (R-001) has final say on what is and is not acceptable. This article cannot be weakened or removed without the explicit agreement of the Party Utility."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "3340532b-d845-5e54-92b3-819ed05365c5",
          "value": "Our right to use this space depends on the trust of the Party Utility and the building community. Demonstrating care of the building is not optional — it is the basis on which the experiment is allowed to continue."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "1f01bc6b-39c8-58d7-b1a3-79142623fece",
          "value": "Unanimous agreement of all current members AND agreement of the Party Utility."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "0df40543-f72a-5471-a7f1-c85c1f1f93e4",
          "value": "Protected — requires Party Utility agreement to amend"
        }
      ],
      "instanceId": "c503fae5-c3ab-452e-a0b4-5682ca204288",
      "lifecycleState": "ratified",
      "typeId": "a1142ac3-5385-5c0e-8630-1dd3432cdf7f",
      "typeName": "article",
      "typeNamespace": "governance",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-08T21:05:17.566879595+00:00"
    },
    "records/tier-2/article-cc58c0dd.json": {
      "createdAt": "2026-05-31T14:55:35.192383646+00:00",
      "fieldValues": [
        {
          "fieldId": "60be1468-01bc-5d12-9eea-628f02801893",
          "value": "A-006"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "d7e82557-9045-5e92-a494-d99112bbec4a",
          "value": "On ending"
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "8aa3eba2-204b-5ebd-ba7a-be0f066027d6",
          "value": "When LiMoMa closes — whether at the end of the pilot, by group decision, or by necessity — the group will: (1) return all artworks to their makers within a reasonable period; (2) remove or make good all fixings and mounts; (3) leave no unresolved commitments to artists, the building, or third parties; (4) transfer any remaining shared funds to the Party Utility for building improvement. The Clerk is responsible for ensuring these obligations are discharged and recorded."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "3340532b-d845-5e54-92b3-819ed05365c5",
          "value": "Ending cleanly is a commitment we make to artists before they show with us, not something we work out at the end. This article makes that commitment concrete."
        },
        {
          "fieldId": "1f01bc6b-39c8-58d7-b1a3-79142623fece",
          "value": "Unanimous agreement of all current members."
        }
      ],
      "instanceId": "cc58c0dd-8e3a-4dc5-9b58-f3273911a9a9",
      "lifecycleState": "ratified",
      "typeId": "a1142ac3-5385-5c0e-8630-1dd3432cdf7f",
      "typeName": "article",
      "typeNamespace": "governance",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-08T21:05:17.669351506+00:00"
    },
    "records/tier-2/decision-2235c7d8.json": {
